{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a1eddb46-b498-4b09-9645-06faa4c460e2","content":"The template is **structurally valid** but has a few gaps before it's NuGet-ready:\n\n**Missing fields:**\n- **`$schema`** — Add `\"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for editor validation.\n- **`description`** — Critical for NuGet discoverability; without it users won't know what the template does.\n- **`groupIdentity`** — Recommended when packaging multiple templates or versioning over time.\n\n**Placeholder concerns:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `author` all look like placeholder values (`MyCompany`, `My Company`). Replace with real branding before publishing.\n\n**Nice-to-haves:**\n- A `dotnet restore` post-action is common for project templates.\n- Consider adding `preferNameDirectory: true`.\n\n**Bottom line:** Add at least a `description` and finalize the placeholder names — then it's ready to ship.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"63c6d10a-93f2-4d8e-bec5-250615e49282","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check against the .NET template engine schema requirements.\n\nIssues I can see:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** – Not strictly required, but strongly recommended for validation and editor support. Should be `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"`.\n\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** – Recommended for NuGet packaging. Helps group related templates.\n\n3. **Missing `precedence`** – Useful when multiple versions of the same template exist.\n\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** – Optional but commonly set for project templates.\n\n\n5. The Framework default of `\"net9.0\"` works, though `net8.0` (LTS) might be safer depending on your audience, and the `sourceName` of `\"MyWebApi\"` is appropriate for namespace replacement. Most critically, there's no `description` field, which is essential for NuGet discoverability—users won't understand what the template provides without it.\n\n6. The template will function without `$schema` and `groupIdentity`, but both are best practices for NuGet publishing. The placeholder values like \"MyCompany\" and \"My Web API Template\" should be replaced with actual metadata before publishing.","outputTokens":714},"id":"d0caf07e-be38-4a34-9ee6-10945e035b58","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:41:56.954Z","parentId":"667f0a95-2338-4a3b-98df-737155752870"}
